CdPS₃ crystallizes in the trigonal R̅3 space group. The structure is two-dimensional and consists of three CdPS₃ sheets oriented in the (0, 0, 1) direction. Cd(1)²⁺ is bonded to six equivalent S(1)²⁻ atoms to form edge-sharing CdS₆ octahedra. There are three shorter (2.727 Å) and three longer (2.777 Å) Cd(1)-S(1) bond lengths. P(1)⁴⁺ is bonded in a trigonal non-coplanar geometry to three equivalent S(1)²⁻ atoms. All P(1)-S(1) bond lengths are 2.046 Å. S(1)²⁻ is bonded in a 3-coordinate geometry to two equivalent Cd(1)²⁺ and one P(1)⁴⁺ atom.

PBr₃ is Ammonia-like structured and crystallizes in the orthorhombic Pnma space group. The structure is zero-dimensional and consists of four PBr₃ clusters. P(1)³⁺ is bonded in a trigonal non-coplanar geometry to one Br(2)¹⁻ and two equivalent Br(1)¹⁻ atoms. The P(1)-Br(2) bond length is 2.271 Å. Both P(1)-Br(1) bond lengths are 2.265 Å. There are two inequivalent Br¹⁻ sites. In the first Br¹⁻ site, Br(1)¹⁻ is bonded in a single-bond geometry to one P(1)³⁺ atom. In the second Br¹⁻ site, Br(2)¹⁻ is bonded in a single-bond geometry to one P(1)³⁺ atom.

VOF crystallizes in the trigonal R̅3m space group. V(1)³⁺ is bonded in a body-centered cubic geometry to four equivalent O(1)²⁻ and four equivalent F(1)¹⁻ atoms. There are three shorter (2.035 Å) and one longer (2.036 Å) V(1)-O(1) bond length. There are three shorter (2.178 Å) and one longer (2.354 Å) V(1)-F(1) bond length. O(1)²⁻ is bonded to four equivalent V(1)³⁺ atoms to form a mixture of edge and corner-sharing OV₄ tetrahedra. F(1)¹⁻ is bonded in a 4-coordinate geometry to four equivalent V(1)³⁺ atoms.

UOTe is Matlockite structured and crystallizes in the tetragonal P4/nmm space group. The structure is two-dimensional and consists of one UOTe sheet oriented in the (0, 0, 1) direction. U(1)⁴⁺ is bonded in a 4-coordinate geometry to four equivalent Te(1)²⁻ and four equivalent O(1)²⁻ atoms. All U(1)-Te(1) bond lengths are 3.208 Å. All U(1)-O(1) bond lengths are 2.328 Å. Te(1)²⁻ is bonded in a 4-coordinate geometry to four equivalent U(1)⁴⁺ atoms. O(1)²⁻ is bonded to four equivalent U(1)⁴⁺ atoms to form a mixture of edge and corner-sharing OU₄ tetrahedra.

InSe is black P-derived structured and crystallizes in the trigonal R3m space group. The structure is two-dimensional and consists of six InSe sheets oriented in the (0, 0, 1) direction. In(1)²⁺ is bonded in a distorted trigonal non-coplanar geometry to three equivalent Se(2)²⁻ atoms. All In(1)-Se(2) bond lengths are 2.678 Å. Se(2)²⁻ is bonded in a distorted trigonal non-coplanar geometry to three equivalent In(1)²⁺ atoms.

CaO₂ crystallizes in the tetragonal I4/mmm space group. Ca(1) is bonded in a distorted q4 geometry to ten equivalent O(1) atoms. There are eight shorter (2.444 Å) and two longer (2.620 Å) Ca(1)-O(1) bond lengths. O(1) is bonded to five equivalent Ca(1) and one O(1) atom to form a mixture of distorted edge, corner, and face-sharing OCa₅O pentagonal pyramids. The O(1)-O(1) bond length is 1.517 Å.

W₂N crystallizes in the trigonal P̅3m1 space group. The structure is two-dimensional and consists of three W₂N sheets oriented in the (0, 0, 1) direction. There are two inequivalent W sites. In the first W site, W(1) is bonded in a 3-coordinate geometry to three equivalent N(2) atoms. All W(1)-N(2) bond lengths are 2.103 Å. In the second W site, W(2) is bonded in a single-bond geometry to one N(2) atom. The W(2)-N(2) bond length is 1.973 Å. N(2) is bonded in a rectangular see-saw-like geometry to one W(2) and three equivalent W(1) atoms.

Hf₃Te₂ crystallizes in the tetragonal I4/mmm space group. The structure is two-dimensional and consists of two Hf₃Te₂ sheets oriented in the (0, 0, 1) direction. There are two inequivalent Hf sites. In the first Hf site, Hf(1) is bonded in a 4-coordinate geometry to four equivalent Te(1) atoms. All Hf(1)-Te(1) bond lengths are 2.945 Å. In the second Hf site, Hf(2) is bonded in a distorted linear geometry to two equivalent Te(1) atoms. Both Hf(2)-Te(1) bond lengths are 3.040 Å. Te(1) is bonded in a 5-coordinate geometry to one Hf(2) and four equivalent Hf(1) atoms.

AgInP₂S₆ crystallizes in the trigonal P̅31c space group. The structure is two-dimensional and consists of two AgInP₂S₆ sheets oriented in the (0, 0, 1) direction. Ag(1)¹⁺ is bonded to six equivalent S(1)²⁻ atoms to form AgS₆ octahedra that share edges with three equivalent In(1)S₆ octahedra. All Ag(1)-S(1) bond lengths are 2.786 Å. In(1)¹⁺ is bonded to six equivalent S(1)²⁻ atoms to form InS₆ octahedra that share edges with three equivalent Ag(1)S₆ octahedra. All In(1)-S(1) bond lengths are 2.687 Å. P(1)⁵⁺ is bonded in a trigonal non-coplanar geometry to three equivalent S(1)²⁻ atoms. All P(1)-S(1) bond lengths are 2.046 Å. S(1)²⁻ is bonded in a 3-coordinate geometry to one Ag(1)¹⁺, one In(1)¹⁺, and one P(1)⁵⁺ atom.

Te₂Br crystallizes in the orthorhombic Pnma space group. The structure is one-dimensional and consists of eight Te clusters and eight TeBr ribbons oriented in the (1, 0, 0) direction. In each Te cluster, Te(2,3)+0.50+ is bonded in a 2-coordinate geometry to  atoms. In each TeBr ribbon, Te(1)+0.50+ is bonded in an L-shaped geometry to two equivalent Br(2)¹⁻ atoms. Both Te(1)-Br(2) bond lengths are 3.056 Å. Br(2)¹⁻ is bonded in an L-shaped geometry to two equivalent Te(1)+0.50+ atoms.

AgO₂Cl crystallizes in the orthorhombic Aem2 space group. The structure is one-dimensional and consists of two AgO₂Cl ribbons oriented in the (1, 0, 0) direction. Ag(1) is bonded in a 3-coordinate geometry to one O(1) and two equivalent O(2) atoms. The Ag(1)-O(1) bond length is 2.176 Å. There is one shorter (2.186 Å) and one longer (2.418 Å) Ag(1)-O(2) bond length. There are two inequivalent O sites. In the first O site, O(1) is bonded in a bent 120 degrees geometry to one Ag(1) and one Cl(1) atom. The O(1)-Cl(1) bond length is 1.585 Å. In the second O site, O(2) is bonded in a 3-coordinate geometry to two equivalent Ag(1) and one Cl(1) atom. The O(2)-Cl(1) bond length is 1.631 Å. Cl(1) is bonded in a water-like geometry to one O(1) and one O(2) atom.

SiP₂ crystallizes in the orthorhombic Pbam space group. The structure is two-dimensional and consists of two SiP₂ sheets oriented in the (0, 0, 1) direction. There are two inequivalent Si⁴⁻ sites. In the first Si⁴⁻ site, Si(1)⁴⁻ is bonded to one P(1)²⁺, one P(3)²⁺, and two equivalent P(2)²⁺ atoms to form corner-sharing SiP₄ tetrahedra. The Si(1)-P(1) bond length is 2.365 Å. The Si(1)-P(3) bond length is 2.290 Å. Both Si(1)-P(2) bond lengths are 2.278 Å. In the second Si⁴⁻ site, Si(2)⁴⁻ is bonded to one P(2)²⁺, one P(4)²⁺, and two equivalent P(3)²⁺ atoms to form corner-sharing SiP₄ tetrahedra. The Si(2)-P(2) bond length is 2.274 Å. The Si(2)-P(4) bond length is 2.300 Å. Both Si(2)-P(3) bond lengths are 2.268 Å. There are four inequivalent P²⁺ sites. In the first P²⁺ site, P(1)²⁺ is bonded in a single-bond geometry to one Si(1)⁴⁻ atom. In the second P²⁺ site, P(2)²⁺ is bonded in a distorted T-shaped geometry to one Si(2)⁴⁻ and two equivalent Si(1)⁴⁻ atoms. In the third P²⁺ site, P(3)²⁺ is bonded in a trigonal non-coplanar geometry to one Si(1)⁴⁻ and two equivalent Si(2)⁴⁻ atoms. In the fourth P²⁺ site, P(4)²⁺ is bonded in a single-bond geometry to one Si(2)⁴⁻ atom.

MoTe₂ crystallizes in the orthorhombic Pmn2₁ space group. The structure is two-dimensional and consists of two MoTe₂ sheets oriented in the (0, 0, 1) direction. Mo(1,2)⁴⁺ is bonded to three equivalent Te(1,3)²⁻ and three equivalent Te(2,4)²⁻ atoms to form distorted edge-sharing MoTe₆ pentagonal pyramids. There are two shorter (2.722 Å) and one longer (2.726 Å) Mo(1,2)-Te(1,3) bond length. There are two shorter (2.829 Å) and one longer (2.850 Å) Mo(1,2)-Te(2,4) bond length. There are two inequivalent Te²⁻ sites. In the first Te²⁻ site, Te(1,3)²⁻ is bonded in a 3-coordinate geometry to three equivalent Mo(1,2)⁴⁺ atoms. In the second Te²⁻ site, Te(2,4)²⁻ is bonded in a 3-coordinate geometry to three equivalent Mo(1,2)⁴⁺ atoms.

PbI₂ is trigonal omega-like structured and crystallizes in the trigonal R̅3m space group. The structure is two-dimensional and consists of three PbI₂ sheets oriented in the (0, 0, 1) direction. Pb(1)²⁺ is bonded to six equivalent I(1)¹⁻ atoms to form edge-sharing PbI₆ octahedra. All Pb(1)-I(1) bond lengths are 3.256 Å. I(1)¹⁻ is bonded in a 3-coordinate geometry to three equivalent Pb(1)²⁺ atoms.

Bi₂Te₂S is MAX Phase-like structured and crystallizes in the trigonal R̅3m space group. The structure is two-dimensional and consists of three Bi₂Te₂S sheets oriented in the (0, 0, 1) direction. Bi(1)³⁺ is bonded to three equivalent Te(1)²⁻ and three equivalent S(1)²⁻ atoms to form a mixture of edge and corner-sharing BiTe₃S₃ octahedra. The corner-sharing octahedra are not tilted. All Bi(1)-Te(1) bond lengths are 3.066 Å. All Bi(1)-S(1) bond lengths are 3.034 Å. Te(1)²⁻ is bonded in a 3-coordinate geometry to three equivalent Bi(1)³⁺ atoms. S(1)²⁻ is bonded to six equivalent Bi(1)³⁺ atoms to form edge-sharing SBi₆ octahedra.

HfCl₄ crystallizes in the monoclinic P2/c space group. The structure is one-dimensional and consists of one HfCl₄ ribbon oriented in the (1, 0, 0) direction. Hf(1)⁴⁺ is bonded to two equivalent Cl(2)¹⁻ and four equivalent Cl(1)¹⁻ atoms to form edge-sharing HfCl₆ octahedra. Both Hf(1)-Cl(2) bond lengths are 2.312 Å. There are two shorter (2.483 Å) and two longer (2.656 Å) Hf(1)-Cl(1) bond lengths. There are two inequivalent Cl¹⁻ sites. In the first Cl¹⁻ site, Cl(1)¹⁻ is bonded in a water-like geometry to two equivalent Hf(1)⁴⁺ atoms. In the second Cl¹⁻ site, Cl(2)¹⁻ is bonded in a single-bond geometry to one Hf(1)⁴⁺ atom.

HfSe₃ crystallizes in the monoclinic P2₁/m space group. The structure is two-dimensional and consists of one HfSe₃ sheet oriented in the (0, 0, 1) direction. Hf(1)⁴⁺ is bonded in a 8-coordinate geometry to two equivalent Se(1)+1.33-, two equivalent Se(2)+1.33-, and four equivalent Se(3)+1.33- atoms. Both Hf(1)-Se(1) bond lengths are 2.736 Å. Both Hf(1)-Se(2) bond lengths are 2.749 Å. There are a spread of Hf(1)-Se(3) bond distances ranging from 2.723-2.890 Å. There are three inequivalent Se+1.33- sites. In the first Se+1.33- site, Se(1)+1.33- is bonded in a 2-coordinate geometry to two equivalent Hf(1)⁴⁺ atoms. In the second Se+1.33- site, Se(2)+1.33- is bonded in a 2-coordinate geometry to two equivalent Hf(1)⁴⁺ atoms. In the third Se+1.33- site, Se(3)+1.33- is bonded to four equivalent Hf(1)⁴⁺ atoms to form a mixture of distorted edge and corner-sharing SeHf₄ trigonal pyramids.

MoO₂ is Cyanogen Chloride-derived structured and crystallizes in the hexagonal P6₃/mmc space group. The structure is zero-dimensional and consists of two MoO₂ clusters. Mo(1)⁴⁺ is bonded in a linear geometry to two equivalent O(1)²⁻ atoms. Both Mo(1)-O(1) bond lengths are 1.764 Å. O(1)²⁻ is bonded in a single-bond geometry to one Mo(1)⁴⁺ atom.

Sc₂C is trigonal omega structured and crystallizes in the trigonal P̅3m1 space group. The structure is two-dimensional and consists of one Sc₂C sheet oriented in the (0, 0, 1) direction. Sc(1)²⁺ is bonded in a distorted T-shaped geometry to three equivalent C(1)⁴⁻ atoms. All Sc(1)-C(1) bond lengths are 2.276 Å. C(1)⁴⁻ is bonded to six equivalent Sc(1)²⁺ atoms to form edge-sharing CSc₆ octahedra.

NdGe₂ crystallizes in the tetragonal I4₁/amd space group. Nd(1) is bonded to twelve equivalent Ge(1) atoms to form a mixture of edge and face-sharing NdGe₁₂ cuboctahedra. There are eight shorter (3.204 Å) and four longer (3.475 Å) Nd(1)-Ge(1) bond lengths. Ge(1) is bonded in a 9-coordinate geometry to six equivalent Nd(1) and three equivalent Ge(1) atoms. There are two shorter (2.551 Å) and one longer (2.600 Å) Ge(1)-Ge(1) bond length.

ScAg(PS₃)₂ crystallizes in the trigonal P̅31c space group. The structure is two-dimensional and consists of two ScAg(PS₃)₂ sheets oriented in the (0, 0, 1) direction. Sc(1)²⁺ is bonded to six equivalent S(1)²⁻ atoms to form ScS₆ octahedra that share edges with three equivalent Ag(1)S₆ octahedra. All Sc(1)-S(1) bond lengths are 2.609 Å. Ag(1)¹⁺ is bonded to six equivalent S(1)²⁻ atoms to form AgS₆ octahedra that share edges with three equivalent Sc(1)S₆ octahedra. All Ag(1)-S(1) bond lengths are 2.806 Å. P(1)+4.50+ is bonded in a trigonal non-coplanar geometry to three equivalent S(1)²⁻ atoms. All P(1)-S(1) bond lengths are 2.044 Å. S(1)²⁻ is bonded in a 3-coordinate geometry to one Sc(1)²⁺, one Ag(1)¹⁺, and one P(1)+4.50+ atom.

Bi₂Te₂Se is MAX Phase-like structured and crystallizes in the trigonal R̅3m space group. The structure is two-dimensional and consists of three Bi₂Te₂Se sheets oriented in the (0, 0, 1) direction. Bi(1)³⁺ is bonded to three equivalent Te(1)²⁻ and three equivalent Se(1)²⁻ atoms to form a mixture of edge and corner-sharing BiTe₃Se₃ octahedra. The corner-sharing octahedra are not tilted. All Bi(1)-Te(1) bond lengths are 3.079 Å. All Bi(1)-Se(1) bond lengths are 3.127 Å. Te(1)²⁻ is bonded in a 3-coordinate geometry to three equivalent Bi(1)³⁺ atoms. Se(1)²⁻ is bonded to six equivalent Bi(1)³⁺ atoms to form edge-sharing SeBi₆ octahedra.

ThNBr is Matlockite structured and crystallizes in the tetragonal P4/nmm space group. The structure is two-dimensional and consists of one ThNBr sheet oriented in the (0, 0, 1) direction. Th(1)⁴⁺ is bonded in a 4-coordinate geometry to four equivalent N(1)³⁻ and four equivalent Br(1)¹⁻ atoms. All Th(1)-N(1) bond lengths are 2.362 Å. All Th(1)-Br(1) bond lengths are 3.344 Å. N(1)³⁻ is bonded to four equivalent Th(1)⁴⁺ atoms to form a mixture of edge and corner-sharing NTh₄ tetrahedra. Br(1)¹⁻ is bonded in a 4-coordinate geometry to four equivalent Th(1)⁴⁺ atoms.

ThI₂ is Molybdenite-like structured and crystallizes in the hexagonal P6₃/mmc space group. The structure is two-dimensional and consists of four ThI₂ sheets oriented in the (0, 0, 1) direction. Th(1) is bonded in a 6-coordinate geometry to six equivalent I(2) atoms. All Th(1)-I(2) bond lengths are 3.224 Å. I(2) is bonded in a 3-coordinate geometry to three equivalent Th(1) atoms.

RhBr₃ is Aluminum trichloride structured and crystallizes in the monoclinic C2/m space group. The structure is two-dimensional and consists of one RhBr₃ sheet oriented in the (0, 0, 1) direction. Rh(1)³⁺ is bonded to two equivalent Br(1)¹⁻ and four equivalent Br(2)¹⁻ atoms to form edge-sharing RhBr₆ octahedra. Both Rh(1)-Br(1) bond lengths are 2.507 Å. There are two shorter (2.501 Å) and two longer (2.503 Å) Rh(1)-Br(2) bond lengths. There are two inequivalent Br¹⁻ sites. In the first Br¹⁻ site, Br(1)¹⁻ is bonded in an L-shaped geometry to two equivalent Rh(1)³⁺ atoms. In the second Br¹⁻ site, Br(2)¹⁻ is bonded in an L-shaped geometry to two equivalent Rh(1)³⁺ atoms.

PdBr₂ crystallizes in the monoclinic C2/c space group. The structure is one-dimensional and consists of two PdBr₂ ribbons oriented in the (0, 0, 1) direction. Pd(1)²⁺ is bonded in a square co-planar geometry to four equivalent Br(1)¹⁻ atoms. There are two shorter (2.466 Å) and two longer (2.467 Å) Pd(1)-Br(1) bond lengths. Br(1)¹⁻ is bonded in an L-shaped geometry to two equivalent Pd(1)²⁺ atoms.

SnSe crystallizes in the orthorhombic Pnma space group. The structure is two-dimensional and consists of two SnSe sheets oriented in the (0, 0, 1) direction. Sn(1)²⁺ is bonded in a 3-coordinate geometry to three equivalent Se(1)²⁻ atoms. There is one shorter (2.789 Å) and two longer (2.830 Å) Sn(1)-Se(1) bond lengths. Se(1)²⁻ is bonded in a 3-coordinate geometry to three equivalent Sn(1)²⁺ atoms.

PtI₂ crystallizes in the monoclinic P2₁/c space group. Pt(1)²⁺ is bonded to three equivalent I(1)¹⁻ and three equivalent I(2)¹⁻ atoms to form a mixture of distorted edge and corner-sharing PtI₆ octahedra. The corner-sharing octahedral tilt angles range from 4-6°. There are a spread of Pt(1)-I(1) bond distances ranging from 2.643-3.513 Å. There are a spread of Pt(1)-I(2) bond distances ranging from 2.628-3.347 Å. There are two inequivalent I¹⁻ sites. In the first I¹⁻ site, I(2)¹⁻ is bonded in a distorted T-shaped geometry to three equivalent Pt(1)²⁺ atoms. In the second I¹⁻ site, I(1)¹⁻ is bonded in a distorted water-like geometry to three equivalent Pt(1)²⁺ atoms.

SmS crystallizes in the tetragonal I4/mmm space group. The structure is two-dimensional and consists of two SmS sheets oriented in the (0, 0, 1) direction. Sm(1)²⁺ is bonded to five equivalent S(1)²⁻ atoms to form a mixture of edge and corner-sharing SmS₅ square pyramids. There are four shorter (2.792 Å) and one longer (2.814 Å) Sm(1)-S(1) bond length. S(1)²⁻ is bonded to five equivalent Sm(1)²⁺ atoms to form a mixture of edge and corner-sharing SSm₅ square pyramids.

ZrNCl crystallizes in the trigonal R̅3m space group. The structure is two-dimensional and consists of three ZrNCl sheets oriented in the (0, 0, 1) direction. Zr(1)⁴⁺ is bonded in a 7-coordinate geometry to four equivalent N(1)³⁻ and three equivalent Cl(1)¹⁻ atoms. There are three shorter (2.142 Å) and one longer (2.183 Å) Zr(1)-N(1) bond length. All Zr(1)-Cl(1) bond lengths are 2.764 Å. N(1)³⁻ is bonded to four equivalent Zr(1)⁴⁺ atoms to form a mixture of edge and corner-sharing NZr₄ tetrahedra. Cl(1)¹⁻ is bonded in a 3-coordinate geometry to three equivalent Zr(1)⁴⁺ atoms.

NaLi₂As crystallizes in the orthorhombic Immm space group. The structure is two-dimensional and consists of two NaLi₂As sheets oriented in the (0, 0, 1) direction. Na(1)¹⁺ is bonded in a distorted rectangular see-saw-like geometry to four equivalent As(1)³⁻ atoms. All Na(1)-As(1) bond lengths are 2.942 Å. Li(1)¹⁺ is bonded in a single-bond geometry to one As(1)³⁻ atom. The Li(1)-As(1) bond length is 2.405 Å. As(1)³⁻ is bonded to four equivalent Na(1)¹⁺ and two equivalent Li(1)¹⁺ atoms to form a mixture of distorted edge and corner-sharing AsNa₄Li₂ octahedra. The corner-sharing octahedra are not tilted.

Lix₀CoO₂ is trigonal omega-like structured and crystallizes in the trigonal R̅3m space group. The structure is two-dimensional and consists of six Lix₀CoO₂ sheets oriented in the (0, 0, 1) direction. Co(1,2)⁴⁺ is bonded to six equivalent O(1,2)²⁻ atoms to form edge-sharing CoO₆ octahedra. All Co(1,2)-O(1,2) bond lengths are 1.876 Å. O(1,2)²⁻ is bonded in a 3-coordinate geometry to three equivalent Co(1,2)⁴⁺ atoms.

AsBr₃ is Ammonia-like structured and crystallizes in the orthorhombic P2_12_12₁ space group. The structure is zero-dimensional and consists of four AsBr₃ clusters. As(1)³⁺ is bonded in a distorted trigonal non-coplanar geometry to one Br(1)¹⁻, one Br(2)¹⁻, and one Br(3)¹⁻ atom. The As(1)-Br(1) bond length is 2.394 Å. The As(1)-Br(2) bond length is 2.391 Å. The As(1)-Br(3) bond length is 2.405 Å. There are three inequivalent Br¹⁻ sites. In the first Br¹⁻ site, Br(2)¹⁻ is bonded in a single-bond geometry to one As(1)³⁺ atom. In the second Br¹⁻ site, Br(1)¹⁻ is bonded in a single-bond geometry to one As(1)³⁺ atom. In the third Br¹⁻ site, Br(3)¹⁻ is bonded in a single-bond geometry to one As(1)³⁺ atom.

Ta₃SeI₇ crystallizes in the hexagonal P6₃mc space group. The structure is two-dimensional and consists of two Ta₃SeI₇ sheets oriented in the (0, 0, 1) direction. Ta(1)³⁺ is bonded to one Se(1)²⁻, one I(3)¹⁻, two equivalent I(1)¹⁻, and two equivalent I(2)¹⁻ atoms to form distorted edge-sharing TaSeI₅ octahedra. The Ta(1)-Se(1) bond length is 2.555 Å. The Ta(1)-I(3) bond length is 3.058 Å. Both Ta(1)-I(1) bond lengths are 2.752 Å. Both Ta(1)-I(2) bond lengths are 2.937 Å. Se(1)²⁻ is bonded in a 3-coordinate geometry to three equivalent Ta(1)³⁺ atoms. There are three inequivalent I¹⁻ sites. In the first I¹⁻ site, I(1)¹⁻ is bonded in a 2-coordinate geometry to two equivalent Ta(1)³⁺ atoms. In the second I¹⁻ site, I(2)¹⁻ is bonded in a water-like geometry to two equivalent Ta(1)³⁺ atoms. In the third I¹⁻ site, I(3)¹⁻ is bonded in a distorted trigonal non-coplanar geometry to three equivalent Ta(1)³⁺ atoms.

PdCl₂ crystallizes in the monoclinic P2₁/c space group. The structure is two-dimensional and consists of one PdCl₂ sheet oriented in the (1, 0, 0) direction. Pd(1)²⁺ is bonded in a square co-planar geometry to four equivalent Cl(1)¹⁻ atoms. There are two shorter (2.330 Å) and two longer (2.332 Å) Pd(1)-Cl(1) bond lengths. Cl(1)¹⁻ is bonded in a water-like geometry to two equivalent Pd(1)²⁺ atoms.

HgI₂ crystallizes in the tetragonal I4₁/amd space group. The structure is two-dimensional and consists of four HgI₂ sheets oriented in the (0, 0, 1) direction. Hg(1)²⁺ is bonded to one I(1)¹⁻, one I(2)¹⁻, and two equivalent I(3)¹⁻ atoms to form corner-sharing HgI₄ tetrahedra. The Hg(1)-I(1) bond length is 2.875 Å. The Hg(1)-I(2) bond length is 2.839 Å. Both Hg(1)-I(3) bond lengths are 2.855 Å. There are three inequivalent I¹⁻ sites. In the first I¹⁻ site, I(1)¹⁻ is bonded in a water-like geometry to two equivalent Hg(1)²⁺ atoms. In the second I¹⁻ site, I(3)¹⁻ is bonded in a water-like geometry to two equivalent Hg(1)²⁺ atoms. In the third I¹⁻ site, I(2)¹⁻ is bonded in a water-like geometry to two equivalent Hg(1)²⁺ atoms.

AuOOH crystallizes in the monoclinic C2/m space group. The structure is two-dimensional and consists of two AuOOH sheets oriented in the (1, 0, 0) direction. Au(1)³⁺ is bonded in a square co-planar geometry to four equivalent O(1)²⁻ atoms. All Au(1)-O(1) bond lengths are 2.024 Å. H(1)¹⁺ is bonded in a linear geometry to two equivalent O(1)²⁻ atoms. Both H(1)-O(1) bond lengths are 1.213 Å. O(1)²⁻ is bonded in a distorted trigonal non-coplanar geometry to two equivalent Au(1)³⁺ and one H(1)¹⁺ atom.

SiSb₃ crystallizes in the hexagonal P6₃/mmc space group. Si(1)⁴⁺ is bonded in a 12-coordinate geometry to twelve equivalent Sb(1)+1.33- atoms. There are six shorter (3.252 Å) and six longer (3.315 Å) Si(1)-Sb(1) bond lengths. Sb(1)+1.33- is bonded in a 12-coordinate geometry to four equivalent Si(1)⁴⁺ and eight equivalent Sb(1)+1.33- atoms. There are a spread of Sb(1)-Sb(1) bond distances ranging from 3.097-3.528 Å.

AlOOH crystallizes in the monoclinic P2₁/m space group. The structure is two-dimensional and consists of one AlOOH sheet oriented in the (0, 0, 1) direction. Ag₃SI crystallizes in the monoclinic P2₁ space group. There are three inequivalent Ag¹⁺ sites. AuOOH crystallizes in the triclinic P̅1 space group. There are two inequivalent Au³⁺ sites. Ni₂SbTe₂ is Calaverite-derived structured and crystallizes in the hexagonal P6₃/mmc space group. PdSCl crystallizes in the monoclinic P2₁/m space group. The structure is one-dimensional and consists of two PdSCl ribbons oriented in the (0, 0, 1) direction. There are four inequivalent Pd³⁺ sites. NbSe₂ is Molybdenite-like structured and crystallizes in the trigonal R3m space group. The structure is two-dimensional and consists of three NbSe₂ sheets oriented in the (0, 0, 1) direction. Mg₂Al₂Se₅ crystallizes in the trigonal P̅3m1 space group. The structure is two-dimensional and consists of one Mg₂Al₂Se₅ sheet oriented in the (0, 0, 1) direction. SbCl₅ is Indium-like structured and crystallizes in the hexagonal P6₃/mmc space group. The structure is zero-dimensional and consists of two SbCl₅ clusters. SnClF is Matlockite structured and crystallizes in the tetragonal P4/nmm space group. The structure is two-dimensional and consists of one SnClF sheet oriented in the (0, 0, 1) direction. PdS₂ crystallizes in the orthorhombic Pbca space group. The structure is two-dimensional and consists of two PdS₂ sheets oriented in the (0, 0, 1) direction. TiZrTe₄ is trigonal omega-derived structured and crystallizes in the monoclinic P2/m space group. TaS₂ is Molybdenite-like structured and crystallizes in the hexagonal P6₃/mmc space group. The structure is two-dimensional and consists of two TaS₂ sheets oriented in the (0, 0, 1) direction. In₂Se₃ crystallizes in the trigonal P̅3m1 space group. The structure is two-dimensional and consists of one In₂Se₃ sheet oriented in the (0, 0, 1) direction. HfTe₃ crystallizes in the monoclinic P2₁/m space group. The structure is two-dimensional and consists of one HfTe₃ sheet oriented in the (0, 0, 1) direction. Bi₂Se₂Te is Calaverite-derived structured and crystallizes in the trigonal R̅3m space group. Rb₂Te is Cotunnite structured and crystallizes in the orthorhombic Pnma space group. There are two inequivalent Rb¹⁺ sites. PdPS crystallizes in the orthorhombic Pbcn space group. Nb₃SiTe₆ crystallizes in the orthorhombic Pnma space group. The structure is two-dimensional and consists of two Nb₃SiTe₆ sheets oriented in the (0, 0, 1) direction. Pd₅AlI₂ crystallizes in the tetragonal I4/mmm space group. The structure is two-dimensional and consists of two Pd₅AlI₂ sheets oriented in the (0, 0, 1) direction. MoO₃ crystallizes in the orthorhombic Pnma space group. The structure is two-dimensional and consists of two MoO₃ sheets oriented in the (0, 0, 1) direction. ScOOH crystallizes in the orthorhombic Cmc2₁ space group. The structure is two-dimensional and consists of two ScOOH sheets oriented in the (0, 1, 0) direction. SrBi₂O₄ crystallizes in the monoclinic C2/m space group. The structure is two-dimensional and consists of two SrBi₂O₄ sheets oriented in the (1, 0, 0) direction. SmZnPO crystallizes in the trigonal R̅3m space group. Sm(1)³⁺ is bonded in a 4-coordinate geometry to three equivalent P(1)³⁻ and four equivalent O(1)²⁻ atoms. Ag₃SnP₇ is Chalcostibite-like structured and crystallizes in the monoclinic P2₁/m space group. There are two inequivalent Ag¹⁺ sites. Sn(1)⁴⁺ is bonded to one Au(1)¹⁻, two equivalent Au(2)¹⁻, one P(2)+0.14-, and two equivalent P(3)+0.14- atoms to form SnP₃Au₃ octahedra that share  a cornercorner with one P(2)SnP₂Au tetrahedra, corners with two equivalent P(3)SnP₂Au tetrahedra, corners with six equivalent P(1)P₂Au₂ tetrahedra, and corners with six equivalent P(4)P₃Au tetrahedra. The Sn(1)-P(2) bond length is 2.680 Å. Both Sn(1)-P(3) bond lengths are 2.676 Å. There are four inequivalent P+0.14- sites. In the first P+0.14- site, P(1)+0.14- is bonded to one Au(1)¹⁻, one Au(2)¹⁻, one P(3)+0.14-, and one P(4)+0.14- atom to form PP₂Au₂ tetrahedra that share corners with three equivalent Sn(1)P₃Au₃ octahedra,  a cornercorner with one P(1)P₂Au₂ tetrahedra, corners with two equivalent P(4)P₃Au tetrahedra, corners with two equivalent P(2)SnP₂Au tetrahedra, and corners with two equivalent P(3)SnP₂Au tetrahedra. The corner-sharing octahedral tilt angles range from 72-87°. The P(1)-P(3) bond length is 2.216 Å. The P(1)-P(4) bond length is 2.242 Å. In the second P+0.14- site, P(2)+0.14- is bonded to one Au(1)¹⁻, one Sn(1)⁴⁺, and two equivalent P(4)+0.14- atoms to form distorted PSnP₂Au tetrahedra that share  a cornercorner with one Sn(1)P₃Au₃ octahedra, corners with four equivalent P(1)P₂Au₂ tetrahedra, and corners with four equivalent P(3)SnP₂Au tetrahedra. The corner-sharing octahedral tilt angles are 28°. Both P(2)-P(4) bond lengths are 2.231 Å. In the third P+0.14- site, P(3)+0.14- is bonded to one Au(2)¹⁻, one Sn(1)⁴⁺, one P(1)+0.14-, and one P(4)+0.14- atom to form distorted PSnP₂Au tetrahedra that share  a cornercorner with one Sn(1)P₃Au₃ octahedra,  a cornercorner with one P(3)SnP₂Au tetrahedra, corners with two equivalent P(1)P₂Au₂ tetrahedra, corners with two equivalent P(4)P₃Au tetrahedra, and corners with two equivalent P(2)SnP₂Au tetrahedra. The corner-sharing octahedral tilt angles are 37°. The P(3)-P(4) bond length is 2.222 Å. In the fourth P+0.14- site, P(4)+0.14- is bonded to one Au(2)¹⁻, one P(1)+0.14-, one P(2)+0.14-, and one P(3)+0.14- atom to form PP₃Au tetrahedra that share corners with three equivalent Sn(1)P₃Au₃ octahedra,  a cornercorner with one P(4)P₃Au tetrahedra, corners with two equivalent P(1)P₂Au₂ tetrahedra, and corners with two equivalent P(3)SnP₂Au tetrahedra. The corner-sharing octahedral tilt angles range from 75-87°.

UO₂Br crystallizes in the orthorhombic Cmcm space group. The structure is two-dimensional and consists of two UO₂Br sheets oriented in the (0, 1, 0) direction. U(1)⁵⁺ is bonded to two equivalent O(1)²⁻, three equivalent O(2)²⁻, and two equivalent Br(1)¹⁻ atoms to form a mixture of distorted edge and corner-sharing UBr₂O₅ pentagonal bipyramids. Both U(1)-O(1) bond lengths are 2.075 Å. There are two shorter (2.177 Å) and one longer (2.308 Å) U(1)-O(2) bond length. Both U(1)-Br(1) bond lengths are 2.958 Å. There are two inequivalent O²⁻ sites. In the first O²⁻ site, O(1)²⁻ is bonded in a linear geometry to two equivalent U(1)⁵⁺ atoms. In the second O²⁻ site, O(2)²⁻ is bonded in a distorted trigonal planar geometry to three equivalent U(1)⁵⁺ atoms. Br(1)¹⁻ is bonded in a 2-coordinate geometry to two equivalent U(1)⁵⁺ atoms.

Bi is alpha As structured and crystallizes in the trigonal R̅3m space group. Bi(1) is bonded to six equivalent Bi(1) atoms to form a mixture of edge and corner-sharing BiBi₆ octahedra. The corner-sharing octahedral tilt angles are 10°. There are three shorter (3.115 Å) and three longer (3.565 Å) Bi(1)-Bi(1) bond lengths.

ZnSe is lead oxide structured and crystallizes in the tetragonal P4/nmm space group. The structure is two-dimensional and consists of one ZnSe sheet oriented in the (0, 0, 1) direction. Zn(1)²⁺ is bonded to four equivalent Se(1)²⁻ atoms to form a mixture of edge and corner-sharing ZnSe₄ tetrahedra. All Zn(1)-Se(1) bond lengths are 2.540 Å. Se(1)²⁻ is bonded in a 4-coordinate geometry to four equivalent Zn(1)²⁺ atoms.

SbSBr crystallizes in the orthorhombic Pnma space group. The structure is one-dimensional and consists of two SbSBr ribbons oriented in the (1, 0, 0) direction. Sb(1)³⁺ is bonded to three equivalent S(1)²⁻ and two equivalent Br(1)¹⁻ atoms to form edge-sharing SbS₃Br₂ square pyramids. There is one shorter (2.527 Å) and two longer (2.691 Å) Sb(1)-S(1) bond lengths. Both Sb(1)-Br(1) bond lengths are 2.969 Å. S(1)²⁻ is bonded in a 3-coordinate geometry to three equivalent Sb(1)³⁺ atoms. Br(1)¹⁻ is bonded in a distorted L-shaped geometry to two equivalent Sb(1)³⁺ atoms.

Na₂Pd₃O₄ crystallizes in the orthorhombic Immm space group. Na(1)¹⁺ is bonded in a 6-coordinate geometry to six equivalent O(1)²⁻ atoms. There are four shorter (2.372 Å) and two longer (2.753 Å) Na(1)-O(1) bond lengths. There are two inequivalent Pd²⁺ sites. In the first Pd²⁺ site, Pd(1)²⁺ is bonded in a square co-planar geometry to four equivalent O(1)²⁻ atoms. All Pd(1)-O(1) bond lengths are 2.056 Å. In the second Pd²⁺ site, Pd(2)²⁺ is bonded in a square co-planar geometry to four equivalent O(1)²⁻ atoms. All Pd(2)-O(1) bond lengths are 2.074 Å. O(1)²⁻ is bonded in a 6-coordinate geometry to three equivalent Na(1)¹⁺, one Pd(2)²⁺, and two equivalent Pd(1)²⁺ atoms.

Nb₃GeTe₆ crystallizes in the orthorhombic Pnma space group. The structure is two-dimensional and consists of two Nb₃GeTe₆ sheets oriented in the (0, 0, 1) direction. There are three inequivalent Nb+2.67+ sites. In the first Nb+2.67+ site, Nb(1)+2.67+ is bonded to two equivalent Te(3)²⁻ and four equivalent Te(2)²⁻ atoms to form distorted edge-sharing NbTe₆ pentagonal pyramids. Both Nb(1)-Te(3) bond lengths are 2.908 Å. There are two shorter (2.829 Å) and two longer (2.852 Å) Nb(1)-Te(2) bond lengths. In the second Nb+2.67+ site, Nb(2)+2.67+ is bonded to two equivalent Te(1)²⁻, two equivalent Te(2)²⁻, and two equivalent Te(3)²⁻ atoms to form a mixture of distorted edge and face-sharing NbTe₆ pentagonal pyramids. Both Nb(2)-Te(1) bond lengths are 2.994 Å. Both Nb(2)-Te(2) bond lengths are 2.784 Å. Both Nb(2)-Te(3) bond lengths are 2.867 Å. In the third Nb+2.67+ site, Nb(3)+2.67+ is bonded to two equivalent Te(3)²⁻ and four equivalent Te(1)²⁻ atoms to form a mixture of distorted edge and face-sharing NbTe₆ pentagonal pyramids. Both Nb(3)-Te(3) bond lengths are 2.985 Å. There are two shorter (2.846 Å) and two longer (2.867 Å) Nb(3)-Te(1) bond lengths. Ge(1)⁴⁺ is bonded in a square co-planar geometry to two equivalent Te(1)²⁻ and two equivalent Te(3)²⁻ atoms. Both Ge(1)-Te(1) bond lengths are 2.862 Å. Both Ge(1)-Te(3) bond lengths are 2.814 Å. There are three inequivalent Te²⁻ sites. In the first Te²⁻ site, Te(1)²⁻ is bonded in a 4-coordinate geometry to one Nb(2)+2.67+, two equivalent Nb(3)+2.67+, and one Ge(1)⁴⁺ atom. In the second Te²⁻ site, Te(2)²⁻ is bonded in a 3-coordinate geometry to one Nb(2)+2.67+ and two equivalent Nb(1)+2.67+ atoms. In the third Te²⁻ site, Te(3)²⁻ is bonded in a 4-coordinate geometry to one Nb(1)+2.67+, one Nb(2)+2.67+, one Nb(3)+2.67+, and one Ge(1)⁴⁺ atom.

Ca₃SiBr₂ is Caswellsilverite-like structured and crystallizes in the orthorhombic Immm space group. There are two inequivalent Ca²⁺ sites. In the first Ca²⁺ site, Ca(1)²⁺ is bonded to two equivalent Si(1)⁴⁻ and four equivalent Br(1)¹⁻ atoms to form a mixture of edge and corner-sharing CaSi₂Br₄ octahedra. The corner-sharing octahedral tilt angles range from 0-20°. Both Ca(1)-Si(1) bond lengths are 2.875 Å. There are two shorter (2.992 Å) and two longer (3.219 Å) Ca(1)-Br(1) bond lengths. In the second Ca²⁺ site, Ca(2)²⁺ is bonded to two equivalent Si(1)⁴⁻ and four equivalent Br(1)¹⁻ atoms to form a mixture of edge and corner-sharing CaSi₂Br₄ octahedra. The corner-sharing octahedra are not tilted. Both Ca(2)-Si(1) bond lengths are 2.948 Å. All Ca(2)-Br(1) bond lengths are 3.233 Å. Si(1)⁴⁻ is bonded to two equivalent Ca(2)²⁺ and four equivalent Ca(1)²⁺ atoms to form SiCa₆ octahedra that share corners with two equivalent Si(1)Ca₆ octahedra, corners with four equivalent Br(1)Ca₆ octahedra, edges with two equivalent Si(1)Ca₆ octahedra, and edges with ten equivalent Br(1)Ca₆ octahedra. The corner-sharing octahedral tilt angles range from 0-7°. Br(1)¹⁻ is bonded to two equivalent Ca(2)²⁺ and four equivalent Ca(1)²⁺ atoms to form BrCa₆ octahedra that share corners with two equivalent Si(1)Ca₆ octahedra, corners with four equivalent Br(1)Ca₆ octahedra, edges with five equivalent Si(1)Ca₆ octahedra, and edges with seven equivalent Br(1)Ca₆ octahedra. The corner-sharing octahedral tilt angles range from 0-20°.

NbSe₂Br₂ is Indium-derived structured and crystallizes in the triclinic P̅1 space group. The structure is zero-dimensional and consists of four Br clusters and one NbSe₂ cluster. In each Br cluster, Br(1,2)+0.50+ is bonded in a 1-coordinate geometry to  atoms. In the NbSe₂ cluster, Nb(1)³⁺ is bonded in a 4-coordinate geometry to two equivalent Se(1)²⁻ and two equivalent Se(2)²⁻ atoms. There is one shorter (2.643 Å) and one longer (2.645 Å) Nb(1)-Se(1) bond length. Both Nb(1)-Se(2) bond lengths are 2.661 Å. There are two inequivalent Se²⁻ sites. In the first Se²⁻ site, Se(1)²⁻ is bonded in a 2-coordinate geometry to two equivalent Nb(1)³⁺ and one Se(2)²⁻ atom. The Se(1)-Se(2) bond length is 2.317 Å. In the second Se²⁻ site, Se(2)²⁻ is bonded in a 3-coordinate geometry to two equivalent Nb(1)³⁺ and one Se(1)²⁻ atom.

Ba₂InO₃Br crystallizes in the tetragonal P4/nmm space group. There are two inequivalent Ba²⁺ sites. In the first Ba²⁺ site, Ba(1)²⁺ is bonded in a 9-coordinate geometry to four equivalent O(1)²⁻ and five equivalent Br(1)¹⁻ atoms. All Ba(1)-O(1) bond lengths are 2.759 Å. There are four shorter (3.302 Å) and one longer (3.629 Å) Ba(1)-Br(1) bond length. In the second Ba²⁺ site, Ba(2)²⁺ is bonded in a 9-coordinate geometry to four equivalent O(1)²⁻ and five equivalent O(2)²⁻ atoms. All Ba(2)-O(1) bond lengths are 3.038 Å. There is one shorter (2.576 Å) and four longer (3.050 Å) Ba(2)-O(2) bond lengths. In(1)³⁺ is bonded to one O(2)²⁻, four equivalent O(1)²⁻, and one Br(1)¹⁻ atom to form distorted corner-sharing InBrO₅ square pyramids. The In(1)-O(2) bond length is 2.107 Å. All In(1)-O(1) bond lengths are 2.175 Å. The In(1)-Br(1) bond length is 3.405 Å. There are two inequivalent O²⁻ sites. In the first O²⁻ site, O(1)²⁻ is bonded in a 6-coordinate geometry to two equivalent Ba(1)²⁺, two equivalent Ba(2)²⁺, and two equivalent In(1)³⁺ atoms. In the second O²⁻ site, O(2)²⁻ is bonded to five equivalent Ba(2)²⁺ and one In(1)³⁺ atom to form a mixture of distorted edge and corner-sharing OBa₅In octahedra. The corner-sharing octahedral tilt angles are 12°. Br(1)¹⁻ is bonded in a 6-coordinate geometry to five equivalent Ba(1)²⁺ and one In(1)³⁺ atom.

AlN is Wurtzite structured and crystallizes in the hexagonal P6₃mc space group. Al(1)³⁺ is bonded to four equivalent N(1)³⁻ atoms to form corner-sharing AlN₄ tetrahedra. There are three shorter (1.903 Å) and one longer (1.915 Å) Al(1)-N(1) bond length. N(1)³⁻ is bonded to four equivalent Al(1)³⁺ atoms to form corner-sharing NAl₄ tetrahedra.

LiAuI₄ crystallizes in the monoclinic P2₁/c space group. The structure is two-dimensional and consists of two LiAuI₄ sheets oriented in the (0, 0, 1) direction. Li(1)¹⁺ is bonded to two equivalent I(2)¹⁻ and four equivalent I(1)¹⁻ atoms to form LiI₆ octahedra that share edges with two equivalent Li(1)I₆ octahedra and edges with four equivalent Au(1)I₆ octahedra. Both Li(1)-I(2) bond lengths are 3.026 Å. There are two shorter (2.957 Å) and two longer (3.019 Å) Li(1)-I(1) bond lengths. Au(1)³⁺ is bonded to two equivalent I(1)¹⁻ and four equivalent I(2)¹⁻ atoms to form distorted AuI₆ octahedra that share edges with two equivalent Au(1)I₆ octahedra and edges with four equivalent Li(1)I₆ octahedra. Both Au(1)-I(1) bond lengths are 2.680 Å. There are two shorter (2.703 Å) and two longer (3.608 Å) Au(1)-I(2) bond lengths. There are two inequivalent I¹⁻ sites. In the first I¹⁻ site, I(2)¹⁻ is bonded in a 2-coordinate geometry to one Li(1)¹⁺ and two equivalent Au(1)³⁺ atoms. In the second I¹⁻ site, I(1)¹⁻ is bonded in a 3-coordinate geometry to two equivalent Li(1)¹⁺ and one Au(1)³⁺ atom.

RhTeCl is Calaverite-derived structured and crystallizes in the monoclinic C2/m space group. Rh(1)³⁺ is bonded to three equivalent Te(1)²⁻ and three equivalent Cl(1)¹⁻ atoms to form edge-sharing RhTe₃Cl₃ octahedra. There are two shorter (2.581 Å) and one longer (2.599 Å) Rh(1)-Te(1) bond length. There is one shorter (2.539 Å) and two longer (2.576 Å) Rh(1)-Cl(1) bond lengths. Te(1)²⁻ is bonded in a 5-coordinate geometry to three equivalent Rh(1)³⁺ and two equivalent Cl(1)¹⁻ atoms. Both Te(1)-Cl(1) bond lengths are 3.712 Å. Cl(1)¹⁻ is bonded in a 3-coordinate geometry to three equivalent Rh(1)³⁺ and two equivalent Te(1)²⁻ atoms.

IrBr₃ is Aluminum trichloride structured and crystallizes in the monoclinic C2/m space group. The structure is two-dimensional and consists of one IrBr₃ sheet oriented in the (0, 0, 1) direction. Ir(1)³⁺ is bonded to two equivalent Br(2)¹⁻ and four equivalent Br(1)¹⁻ atoms to form edge-sharing IrBr₆ octahedra. Both Ir(1)-Br(2) bond lengths are 2.517 Å. There are two shorter (2.513 Å) and two longer (2.515 Å) Ir(1)-Br(1) bond lengths. There are two inequivalent Br¹⁻ sites. In the first Br¹⁻ site, Br(1)¹⁻ is bonded in an L-shaped geometry to two equivalent Ir(1)³⁺ atoms. In the second Br¹⁻ site, Br(2)¹⁻ is bonded in an L-shaped geometry to two equivalent Ir(1)³⁺ atoms.

Li₂CeAs₂ crystallizes in the trigonal P̅3m1 space group. Li(1)¹⁺ is bonded to four equivalent As(1)³⁻ atoms to form LiAs₄ tetrahedra that share corners with six equivalent Ce(1)As₆ octahedra, corners with six equivalent Li(1)As₄ tetrahedra, edges with three equivalent Ce(1)As₆ octahedra, and edges with three equivalent Li(1)As₄ tetrahedra. The corner-sharing octahedral tilt angles range from 11-57°. There are three shorter (2.639 Å) and one longer (2.660 Å) Li(1)-As(1) bond length. Ce(1)⁴⁺ is bonded to six equivalent As(1)³⁻ atoms to form CeAs₆ octahedra that share corners with twelve equivalent Li(1)As₄ tetrahedra, edges with six equivalent Ce(1)As₆ octahedra, and edges with six equivalent Li(1)As₄ tetrahedra. All Ce(1)-As(1) bond lengths are 2.930 Å. As(1)³⁻ is bonded to four equivalent Li(1)¹⁺ and three equivalent Ce(1)⁴⁺ atoms to form a mixture of distorted edge and corner-sharing AsLi₄Ce₃ pentagonal bipyramids.

As₂O₃ crystallizes in the monoclinic P2₁/c space group. The structure is two-dimensional and consists of two As₂O₃ sheets oriented in the (0, 1, 0) direction. There are two inequivalent As³⁺ sites. In the first As³⁺ site, As(1)³⁺ is bonded in a distorted T-shaped geometry to one O(1)²⁻, one O(2)²⁻, and one O(3)²⁻ atom. The As(1)-O(1) bond length is 1.832 Å. The As(1)-O(2) bond length is 1.832 Å. The As(1)-O(3) bond length is 1.853 Å. In the second As³⁺ site, As(2)³⁺ is bonded in a distorted trigonal non-coplanar geometry to one O(1)²⁻, one O(2)²⁻, and one O(3)²⁻ atom. The As(2)-O(1) bond length is 1.834 Å. The As(2)-O(2) bond length is 1.812 Å. The As(2)-O(3) bond length is 1.827 Å. There are three inequivalent O²⁻ sites. In the first O²⁻ site, O(1)²⁻ is bonded in a bent 120 degrees geometry to one As(1)³⁺ and one As(2)³⁺ atom. In the second O²⁻ site, O(2)²⁻ is bonded in a distorted bent 120 degrees geometry to one As(1)³⁺ and one As(2)³⁺ atom. In the third O²⁻ site, O(3)²⁻ is bonded in a bent 120 degrees geometry to one As(1)³⁺ and one As(2)³⁺ atom.

P₂NbS₈ is I4/mcm-derived structured and crystallizes in the orthorhombic Cmce space group. The structure is two-dimensional and consists of two P₂NbS₈ sheets oriented in the (0, 0, 1) direction. Nb(1)⁵⁺ is bonded in a 8-coordinate geometry to two equivalent S(2)+1.88-, two equivalent S(3)+1.88-, two equivalent S(4)+1.88-, and two equivalent S(5)+1.88- atoms. Both Nb(1)-S(2) bond lengths are 2.525 Å. Both Nb(1)-S(3) bond lengths are 2.544 Å. Both Nb(1)-S(4) bond lengths are 2.632 Å. Both Nb(1)-S(5) bond lengths are 2.680 Å. P(1)⁵⁺ is bonded to one S(4)+1.88-, one S(5)+1.88-, and two equivalent S(1)+1.88- atoms to form edge-sharing PS₄ tetrahedra. The P(1)-S(4) bond length is 2.015 Å. The P(1)-S(5) bond length is 2.001 Å. There is one shorter (2.117 Å) and one longer (2.159 Å) P(1)-S(1) bond length. There are five inequivalent S+1.88- sites. In the first S+1.88- site, S(1)+1.88- is bonded in an L-shaped geometry to two equivalent P(1)⁵⁺ atoms. In the second S+1.88- site, S(2)+1.88- is bonded in a 3-coordinate geometry to two equivalent Nb(1)⁵⁺ and one S(3)+1.88- atom. The S(2)-S(3) bond length is 2.033 Å. In the third S+1.88- site, S(3)+1.88- is bonded in a 3-coordinate geometry to two equivalent Nb(1)⁵⁺ and one S(2)+1.88- atom. In the fourth S+1.88- site, S(4)+1.88- is bonded in an L-shaped geometry to one Nb(1)⁵⁺ and one P(1)⁵⁺ atom. In the fifth S+1.88- site, S(5)+1.88- is bonded in an L-shaped geometry to one Nb(1)⁵⁺ and one P(1)⁵⁺ atom.

HoSI crystallizes in the orthorhombic Pmmn space group. The structure is two-dimensional and consists of one HoSI sheet oriented in the (0, 0, 1) direction. Ho(1)³⁺ is bonded to four equivalent S(1)²⁻ and two equivalent I(1)¹⁻ atoms to form a mixture of edge and corner-sharing HoS₄I₂ octahedra. The corner-sharing octahedral tilt angles are 19°. There are two shorter (2.700 Å) and two longer (2.730 Å) Ho(1)-S(1) bond lengths. Both Ho(1)-I(1) bond lengths are 3.020 Å. S(1)²⁻ is bonded to four equivalent Ho(1)³⁺ atoms to form a mixture of distorted edge and corner-sharing SHo₄ trigonal pyramids. I(1)¹⁻ is bonded in an L-shaped geometry to two equivalent Ho(1)³⁺ atoms.

TaSe₂ is Molybdenite-like structured and crystallizes in the trigonal R3m space group. The structure is two-dimensional and consists of six TaSe₂ sheets oriented in the (0, 0, 1) direction. Ta(1)⁴⁺ is bonded to six equivalent Se(1,3)²⁻ atoms to form edge-sharing TaSe₆ octahedra. There are three shorter (2.609 Å) and three longer (2.610 Å) Ta(1)-Se(1,3) bond lengths. Se(1,3)²⁻ is bonded in a 3-coordinate geometry to three equivalent Ta(1)⁴⁺ atoms.

LuPb₂ crystallizes in the tetragonal I4/mmm space group. The structure is two-dimensional and consists of two LuPb₂ sheets oriented in the (0, 0, 1) direction. Lu(1) is bonded in a body-centered cubic geometry to eight equivalent Pb(1) atoms. All Lu(1)-Pb(1) bond lengths are 3.280 Å. Pb(1) is bonded in a 4-coordinate geometry to four equivalent Lu(1) atoms.
